From: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
Date: Wed, 15 Jan 2014 10:52:18 +0100
Subject: scsi_dh_alua: fixup misplaced brace in alua_initialize()
References: bnc#858831
Patch-Mainline: submitted to linux-scsi

There was a misplaced brace in alua_initialize(), which might
cause a kernel oops during boot.

Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/device_handler/scsi_dh_alua.c b/drivers/scsi/device_handler/scsi_dh_alua.c
index 785b374..16877f8 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/device_handler/scsi_dh_alua.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/device_handler/scsi_dh_alua.c
@@ -1062,8 +1062,8 @@ static int alua_initialize(struct scsi_device *sdev, struct alua_dh_data *h)
 	if (pg) {
 		pg->expiry = 0;
 		alua_rtpg_queue(pg, sdev, NULL);
+		kref_put(&pg->kref, release_port_group);
 	}
-	kref_put(&pg->kref, release_port_group);
 	return h->error;
 }
 
